<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="Patrick" data-post="35" data-topic="4557">
<div class="title">
<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img alt width="20" height="20" src="../../../../external.html?link=http://forums.whonix.org/user_avatar/forums.whonix.org/patrick/40/17_2.png" class="avatar"> Patrick:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>If attacker can remotely enable OEM unlocking they already do have root access?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>The purpose of verified boot is to prevent the attacker from <em>persisting</em> as root. It doesn’t matter if the attacker has unlimited capabilities, verified boot will still revert their changes.</p>
